[0.000, "o", "\u001b[2K\u001b[1A\u001b[2K\u001b[1A\u001b[2K\u001b[1A\u001b[2K\u001b[1A\u001b[2K\u001b[1A\u001b[2K\u001b[1A\u001b[2K\u001b[1A\u001b[2K\u001b[1A\u001b[2K\u001b[1A\u001b[2K\u001b[1A\u001b[2K\u001b[1A\u001b[2K\u001b[1A\u001b[2K\u001b[1A\u001b[2K\u001b[1A\u001b[2K\u001b[1A\u001b[2K\u001b[1A\u001b[2K\u001b[1A\u001b[2K\u001b[1A\u001b[2K\u001b[1A\u001b[2K\u001b[1A\u001b[2K\u001b[1A\u001b[2K\u001b[1A\u001b[2K\u001b[1A\u001b[2K\u001b[1A\u001b[2K\u001b[1A\u001b[2K\u001b[1A\u001b[2K\u001b[1A\u001b[2K\u001b[1A\u001b[2K\u001b[1A\u001b[2K\u001b[1A\u001b[2K\u001b[1A\u001b[2K\u001b[1A\u001b[2K\u001b[1A\u001b[2K\u001b[1A\u001b[2K\u001b[1A\u001b[2K\u001b[1A\u001b[2K\u001b[1A\u001b[2K\u001b[1A\u001b[2K\u001b[1A\u001b[2K\u001b[1A\u001b[2K\u001b[1A\u001b[2K\u001b[1A\u001b[2K\u001b[1A\u001b[2K\u001b[1A\u001b[2K\u001b[1A\u001b[2K\u001b[1A\u001b[2K\u001b[1A\u001b[2K\u001b[1A\u001b[2K\u001b[1A\u001b[2K\u001b[1A\u001b[2K\u001b[1A\u001b[2K\u001b[1A\u001b[2K\u001b[1A\u001b[2K\u001b[G\u001b[1m\u001b[36mPreview\u001b[22m\u001b[32m my-saas\u001b[39m\u001b[2m a1b2c3d4...  12 messages\u001b[22m\r\n\r\n\u001b[37m\u001b[2m     \u001b[22m- src/auth/session.ts\u001b[39m\r\n\u001b[37m\u001b[2m     \u001b[22m- src/auth/refresh.ts\u001b[39m\r\n\u001b[37m\u001b[2m     \u001b[22m- src/middleware/auth.ts\u001b[39m\r\n\u001b[2m────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\u001b[22m\r\n\u001b[1m\u001b[32mYou: \u001b[22mThe token is stored in localStorage but it seems like the refresh token rotation isn't working\u001b[39m\r\n\u001b[2m───────────────────"]
[0.000, "o", "─────────────────────────────────────────\u001b[22m\r\n\u001b[37m\u001b[2mAI:  \u001b[22mFound the issue. In `auth/refresh.ts`, the rotation logic calls `revokeToken()` before the new\u001b[39m\r\n\u001b[37m\u001b[2m     \u001b[22mtoken is saved. If the save fails, the user loses both tokens.\u001b[39m\r\n\u001b[37m\u001b[2m     \u001b[22m\u001b[39m\r\n\u001b[37m\u001b[2m     \u001b[22mHere's what's happening step by step:\u001b[39m\r\n\u001b[37m\u001b[2m     \u001b[22m\u001b[39m\r\n\u001b[37m\u001b[2m     \u001b[22m1. User's access token expires\u001b[39m\r\n\u001b[37m\u001b[2m     \u001b[22m2. Client calls /api/auth/refresh with the refresh token\u001b[39m\r\n\u001b[37m\u001b[2m     \u001b[22m3. Server generates new access + refresh tokens\u001b[39m\r\n\u001b[37m\u001b[2m     \u001b[22m4. Server revokes the old refresh token  <-- this happens first\u001b[39m\r\n\u001b[37m\u001b[2m     \u001b[22m5. Server sends new tokens to client\u001b[39m\r\n\u001b[37m\u001b[2m     \u001b[22m6. Client saves to localStorage  <-- if this fails, user is locked out\u001b[39m\r\n\u001b[37m\u001b[2m     \u001b[22m\u001b[39m\r\n\u001b[37m\u001b[2m     \u001b[22mThe fix is to reorder steps 4 and 6:\u001b[39m\r\n\u001b[37m\u001b[2m     \u001b[22m1. Sav"]
[0.000, "o", "e the new token first\u001b[39m\r\n\u001b[37m\u001b[2m     \u001b[22m2. Then revoke the old one\u001b[39m\r\n\u001b[37m\u001b[2m     \u001b[22m3. Add a try-catch to handle save failures gracefully\u001b[39m\r\n\u001b[37m\u001b[2m     \u001b[22m\u001b[39m\r\n\u001b[37m\u001b[2m     \u001b[22mLet me implement this now.\u001b[39m\r\n\u001b[2m────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\u001b[22m\r\n\u001b[1m\u001b[32mYou: \u001b[22mThat makes sense. Can you also add a test for this?\u001b[39m\r\n\u001b[2m────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\u001b[22m\r\n\u001b[37m\u001b[2mAI:  \u001b[22mDone. I've updated `auth/refresh.ts` with the new order and added comprehensive tests.\u001b[39m\r\n\u001b[37m\u001b[2m     \u001b[22m\u001b[39m\r\n\u001b[37m\u001b[2m     \u001b[22mChanges made:\u001b[39m\r\n\u001b[37m\u001b[2m     \u001b[22m\u001b[39m\r\n\u001b[37m\u001b[2m     \u001b[22m**src/auth/refresh.ts**\u001b[39m\r\n\u001b[37m\u001b[2m     \u001b[22m- Reordered token rotation: save first, revoke second\u001b[39"]
[0.000, "o", "m\r\n\u001b[37m\u001b[2m     \u001b[22m- Added try-catch around localStorage.setItem\u001b[39m\r\n\u001b[37m\u001b[2m     \u001b[22m- Added fallback: if save fails, keep old tokens valid\u001b[39m\r\n\u001b[37m\u001b[2m     \u001b[22m- Added logging for debugging token rotation issues\u001b[39m\r\n\u001b[37m\u001b[2m     \u001b[22m\u001b[39m\r\n\u001b[37m\u001b[2m     \u001b[22m**tests/auth/refresh.test.ts** (new file)\u001b[39m\r\n\u001b[37m\u001b[2m     \u001b[22m- Test: normal refresh flow works end-to-end\u001b[39m\r\n\u001b[37m\u001b[2m     \u001b[22m- Test: failed localStorage save keeps old token valid\u001b[39m\r\n\u001b[37m\u001b[2m     \u001b[22m- Test: concurrent refresh requests are serialized\u001b[39m\r\n\u001b[37m\u001b[2m     \u001b[22m- Test: expired refresh token returns 401\u001b[39m\r\n\u001b[37m\u001b[2m     \u001b[22m- Test: invalid refresh token returns 403\u001b[39m\r\n\u001b[37m\u001b[2m     \u001b[22m\u001b[39m\r\n\u001b[37m\u001b[2m     \u001b[22mAll 5 tests passing.\u001b[39m\r\n\u001b[2m────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\u001b[22m\r\n\u001b[1m\u001b[32mYou: \u001b[22mNice. One more thing - can we add a retry mechanism? Somet"]
